TITLE: Iconic Russian singer asks to be named ‘foreign agent’ in solidarity with husband
SUMMARY: Alla Pugacheva says she wants to be placed on Russia's foreign agents list in solidarity with her husband Maxim Galkin who has been designated as one.

TITLE: What to expect from NYC’s UN General Assembly traffic nightmare
SUMMARY: Bus routes will be disrupted and roads closed — sometimes without notice — generally turning Midtown into a gridlock nightmare for drivers all week while world leaders convene on First Avenue between 42nd and 48th streets.

TITLE: ‘Phantom of the Opera’ sales explode after shock closing announcement
SUMMARY: After The Post’s Friday scoop that the show would close this winter after 35 years, it took in $2 million in ticket sales by 8 p.m., producer Cameron Mackintosh exclusively told The Post.

TITLE: Aaron Judge hits 58th home run to get within three of Roger Maris
SUMMARY: Aaron Judge is getting closer to making history.

TITLE: Knicks sign Ukrainian wing Svi Mykhailiuk
SUMMARY: Svi Mykhailiuk helped Ukraine to a Round of 16 run at Eurobasket.

TITLE: Democrat El Paso Mayor Oscar Leeser says he sent migrants to NYC ‘to help them’
SUMMARY: "The people are not coming to El Paso, they're coming to America, and that's something that's really important," Mayor Oscar Leeser said in an appearance on ABC's "This Week."

TITLE: Grimes shares pic of bandaged face after saying she wanted ‘elf ear’ surgery
SUMMARY: The singer shared a photo of her face all bandaged up via Twitter on Saturday after previously telling fans that she wanted to get “elf ear” surgery.

TITLE: Madman seen smashing NYC McDonald’s with an ax released without bail
SUMMARY: Michael Palacios was arraigned on fourth-degree criminal-mischief and possession-of-weapons charges.

TITLE: GOP exposing broken immigration system under Biden with migrant buses: Sen. Mike Rounds
SUMMARY: "They're doing their best to try to send a message to the rest of the nation about the plight of those individuals that are coming from south of the border​," said Sen. Mike Rounds.

TITLE: NFL Sunday Ticket goes down and leaves everyone furious
SUMMARY: The last year of Sunday Ticket on DirecTV is off to a rough start.

TITLE: Tom Brady has another tablet-tossing meltdown in Buccaneers game
SUMMARY: A new NFL season means a new year of players throwing Microsoft Surface tablets on the sidelines when things aren't going their way.

TITLE: Joan Hodges, widow of Mets manager Gil Hodges, dead at 95
SUMMARY: Joan Hodges, the widow of former Mets manager and Hall of Famer Gil Hodges, died on Saturday night after a long illness.
